author: Reuters Editorial
title: U.S. 5-year note sold at highest yield since 2008
text:
NEW YORK, April 25 (Reuters) - The U.S. Treasury Department on Wednesday sold $35 billion of five-year government notes at a yield of 2.837 percent, the highest yield at an auction of this debt maturity since September 2008, Treasury data showed.
The ratio of bids to the amount of five-year notes offered was 2.49, a shade below the 2.50 at the prior five-year auction held in March. (Reporting by Richard Leong Editing by James Dalgleish)
